chargeHist.descr: Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction

result.execSummary:
The defendant David Christopher Turner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery to Injunction Petitioner [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.20(1m)(a).
  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Original Transcript SENTENCING (14 pages) commencing AUGUST 28, 2015 received and filed.
Count one.
Count two.

Defendant David Christopher Turner in court with attorney Eric Richard Hart.  Defendant David Christopher Turner in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties.
As to count 1:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 33 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 128 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 16 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 17 MONTHS with the following conditions:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and restitution, if any, be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges.  All costs, assessements and surcharges ordered in count 2 to be paid during ES on this count.
-Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence.
The defendant is given a written explanation of the determinate sentence, and advised of his appeal rights by defense counsel.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.   
As to count 2:    The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 1 with credit for 0 days time served.  The court orders all costs, assessments and surcharges to be paid during Extended Supervision on  count 1.  FAILURE TO DO SO WILL RESULT IN ENTRY OF CIVIL JUDGMENT.
Defendant remanded.  
Filed:  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief; Written Explanation Determinate Sentence; Pretrial Sentence Credit

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

AS TO COUNT 3
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on motion of the state, court ordered count 3 Dismissed, but Read In. 

Case adjourned to branch 38 for Sentencing.

Defendant David Christopher Turner in court with attorney Eric Richard Hart.  Defendant David Christopher Turner in custody.  Grant Ian Huebner appeared on behalf of Nicholas Heitman for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Parties have reached a resolution. 

AS TO COUNT 1
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Battery to Injunction Petitioner, Domestic Abuse Assessments contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.20(1m)(a) and 973.055(1), a Class I Felony.

AS TO COUNT 2
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order- Injunction, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 813.12(8)(a), a Class U Misdemeanor.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 28, 2015 at 08:15 am.
